# Documentation Output Path Rules

## Default Behavior

- Generated documentation should be saved to the `docs/` directory in the
  project root by default
- Environment variable `MCP_DOCS_OUTPUT_PATH` can override this default path
- Relative paths are resolved relative to project root, absolute paths are used as-is

## Examples

- `export MCP_DOCS_OUTPUT_PATH="generated-docs"` → saves to `project/generated-docs/`
- `export MCP_DOCS_OUTPUT_PATH="/tmp/docs"` → saves to `/tmp/docs/`
- No env var set → saves to `project/docs/` (default)

## Template Usage

- When `template_apply` is called with empty `output_path`, auto-generate
  filename in docs directory
- Template ID becomes the filename (e.g., `architecture-doc` → `architecture-doc.md`)
- Always ensure the output directory exists before writing files
